    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix ASN.1 encoding error in RRC reestablishment request\n\n### Summary\nThe RRC reestablishment procedure was failing due to malformed ASN.1 encoded messages. Investigation revealed that the `do_RRCReestablishmentRequest` function had two critical issues:\n\n1. Stack-allocated buffer for `shortMAC-I` field that could become invalid during encoding\n2. Insufficient buffer size (100 bytes) for ASN.1 encoding causing truncation\n\nThese issues caused the encoded RRCReestablishmentRequest message to be malformed, leading to rejection by the network.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/MESSAGES/asn1_msg.c`: \n  - Changed `shortMAC-I` buffer allocation from stack to heap in `do_RRCReestablishmentRequest`\n  - Increased encoding buffer size from 100 to 1024 bytes in `do_RRCReestablishmentRequest`\n  - Added proper memory cleanup with `free()` instead of NULL assignment\n  - Increased buffer size in `do_NR_SA_UECapabilityEnquiry` from 100 to 1024 bytes\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the original issue:\n1. Configure UE to trigger RRC reestablishment procedure\n2. Observe ASN.1 encoding failures in logs\n3. Network rejects malformed RRCReestablishmentRequest messages\n4. UE fails to reestablish connection and goes to idle state\n\nAfter fix, RRC reestablishment procedure completes successfully with properly encoded messages.\n"
}